Key Match Events: Pakistan defeated Ireland by six wickets in the third and final T20I to clinch the series 2-1.
Pakistan won the toss and opted to bowl first in the third T20I against Ireland in Dublin.
Ireland scored 125 runs for the loss of two wickets after 12.5 overs, with Lorcan Tucker batting on 72 off 39 balls.
Pakistan chased down Ireland's target of 179 runs with six wickets and 18 balls to spare.
Post-Match Reflections: Pakistan will now head to England to embark on a four-match T20I series, starting May 22.
